02:04:08,066 --> 02:04:12,070
Her special area of study is...

1051
02:04:15,490 --> 02:04:16,741
I'll get it.

1052
02:04:20,662 --> 02:04:21,663
Hello?

1053
02:04:21,746 --> 02:04:23,456
<i>Elio, you there?</i>

1054
02:04:24,582 --> 02:04:26,668
- Hi.
<i>- Hey.</i>

1055
02:04:27,210 --> 02:04:29,045
- How are you.
<i>- I'm good.</i>

1056
02:04:29,712 --> 02:04:30,797
<i>I'm good. How are you?</i>

1057
02:04:30,880 --> 02:04:32,548
<i>- How are your parents?</i>
- I'm good. They're fine.

1058
02:04:33,132 --> 02:04:34,258
<i>Good.</i>

1059
02:04:36,094 --> 02:04:37,220
I miss you.

1060
02:04:38,638 --> 02:04:39,806
<i>I miss you too.</i>

1061
02:04:41,057 --> 02:04:42,100
<i>Very much.</i>

1062
02:04:46,312 --> 02:04:48,982
<i>- I have some news.</i>
- News?

1063
02:04:51,818 --> 02:04:53,403
What, you're getting married?

1064
02:04:53,903 --> 02:04:55,071
I suppose.

1065
02:04:57,448 --> 02:04:59,993
<i>I might be getting married
next spring, yeah.</i>

1066
02:05:03,579 --> 02:05:05,248
You never said anything.

1067
02:05:07,375 --> 02:05:09,544
<i>Been off and on for three years.</i>

1068
02:05:13,589 --> 02:05:14,924
That's wonderful news.

1069
02:05:17,135 --> 02:05:18,261
<i>Do you mind?</i>

1070
02:05:25,601 --> 02:05:26,769
- Oliver.
- Oliver.

1071
02:05:26,853 --> 02:05:28,855
- Oliver.
<i>- Hey, hey, hey.</i>

1072
02:05:28,938 --> 02:05:30,231
Darling, when are you coming back?

1073
02:05:30,857 --> 02:05:32,150
<i>I wish I was.</i>

1074
02:05:32,483 --> 02:05:35,903
You caught us in the process of choosing
the new you for next summer.

1075
02:05:36,154 --> 02:05:38,656
- And guess what? He's a she.
<i>- Oh, no.</i>

1076
02:05:38,740 --> 02:05:41,451
<i>Speaking of she's, I'm calling
to tell you guys I got engaged.</i>

1077
02:05:43,411 --> 02:05:45,538
Wonderful!

1078
02:05:45,621 --> 02:05:47,498
- Congratulations.
- Mazel tov!

1079
02:05:47,582 --> 02:05:49,667
- Congratulations, Oliver.
<i>- Thank you, thank you, thank you.</i>

1080
02:05:49,751 --> 02:05:53,129
Listen, we'll leave you...
We'll let you speak to Elio.

1081
02:05:53,337 --> 02:05:55,423
- Happy Hanukkah!
<i>- Happy Hanukkah!</i>

1082
02:05:55,506 --> 02:05:56,632
Bye, sweetheart.

1083
02:06:04,390 --> 02:06:05,808
They know about us.

1084
02:06:07,268 --> 02:06:08,436
<i>I figured.</i>

1085
02:06:10,897 --> 02:06:12,148
How?

1086
02:06:13,900 --> 02:06:15,777
<i>Well, from the way your dad spoke to me.</i>

1087
02:06:17,195 --> 02:06:19,113
<i>He made me feel
like I was a part of the family.</i>

1088
02:06:19,697 --> 02:06:20,990
<i>Almost like a son-in-law.</i>

1089
02:06:23,201 --> 02:06:24,327
<i>You're so lucky.</i>

1090
02:06:25,912 --> 02:06:28,706
<i>My father would have carted me off
to a correctional facility.</i>

1091
02:06:31,250 --> 02:06:32,502
Elio.

1092
02:06:36,130 --> 02:06:40,176
Elio. Elio. Elio. Elio.
Elio. Elio. Elio. Elio.

1093
02:06:43,846 --> 02:06:45,348
<i>Oliver.</i>

1094
02:06:48,226 --> 02:06:49,769
<i>I remember everything.</i>

1095
02:10:54,638 --> 02:10:55,931
Elio.

1096
02:10:58,184 --> 02:10:59,185
Elio.

